<TITLE> BTTB cuts digital landline rents </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 8 (bdnews24.com)  Authorities have revised line rents for BTTB digital land phones and shifting fees of telephones, effective from August 1, the government said in a statement Wednesday. Monthly line rents have been fixed at Tk 100 for divisional headquarters and district towns, except for Dhaka and Chittagong, and Tk 50 for upazilas, down from the earlier flat rate at Tk 150. In the multi-exchange areas such as Dhaka and Chittagong, line rents remain unchanged. Fees for shifting telephone lines were reset at Tk 1,500 for Dhaka and Chittagong, while Tk 1,000 has been fixed for other divisional cities and district towns and Tk 500 for upazilas, down from the previous flat rate at Tk 2,500. bd
